{{DISPLAYTITLE: <span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF"> Level 243: "Dark Slums" </span>}} {{Background|file=Level243 1.png}}
{{Class Custom Image|hexagon=E|bg-image=Level243 1.png|text-color=white|class=4e - Environmental|safety=Unsafe|security=Unstable|entity=Non-Entity Related Hazards}}
<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''Level 243''' is the 244<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms. This level was discovered by an unknown individual on April 19<sup>th</sup>, 2024.<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:verdana; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">''Description''</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Level243 1.png|caption=Image of one of the building on the Level 243.|align=right|hovertext=The wind is starting to get cold...}}
{{Audio|file=Wind_ambience_hell_yeah.mp3|align=right|volume=0.75|loop=yes}}
<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''Level 243''' resembless an endless city immersed in almost eternal twilight. Buildings in this level mostly share similarities with [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panel_building panel houses], whose height is approximately 12 to 32 floors high. The layout of this city consists of almost identical, endlessly repeating blocks. In rare cases, their geometry can be too illogical and [[Phenomenon 14|not subject to the laws of physics]]. The sky at level, even during daylight hours, is a perpetual navy blue. The earth in its natural form is not visible at this level, as the ground is mostly covered with asphalt roads and sidewalks. There are small patches near the buildings where grass grows. The surface may be slightly damp or have puddles. At street intersections, there are no traffic lights and no road markings of any kind, which distinguishes this level from '''[[Level 11]]'''.

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">The buildings on '''Level 243''' are mostly made of brick, but occasionally made of concrete. Plaster or bricks can fall off the walls in rare cases, so it is not recommended to walk too close to buildings that look crumbling or overly aged ''(this can be recognized by the moss penetrating the building and the cracks in its foundation)''. <span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">It is impossible to enter buildings, but sometimes doors may appear on the walls; most often, they are out of reach. There is nothing inside except for a few objects, being mostly just a concrete base. Occasionally, there may be planks, tools, or very rarely, a wall clock that accurately shows the time. <span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">As darkness falls, lights may appear in the windows of houses, but their source has not been determined, as there are no working light bulbs or entities in the buildings that could emit light.

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''Level 243''' is also not particularly cold, about <u>66,2°</u> Fahrenheit ''(19° Celsius)''. Closer to the night, the temperature will begin to drop to <u>14°</u> Fahrenheit ''(-10° Celsius)'', and there is a significant risk of dying from hypothermia without warm clothing. Although the temperatures drop below 0º Celsius, there is no snow in this level. The lighting of [[Level 243]] is dim due to thick clouds covering the sunlight. During the daytime, the level is relatively safe. Before sunset, the clouds may clear slightly; the reason for this phenomenon is unknown. Sometimes precipitation may occur; the composition of the water that falls is similar to the water on '''[[Level 37]]''', as it also includes [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnesium_sulfate '''magnesium sulfate'''] ''(or so-called «epsom salts»)''. If this substance is absorbed into the body of the wanderer, it will have a relaxing effect on the body and the muscles, relieving pain. Precipitation falls quite rarely, and rain lasts about half an hour. After precipitation ceases, all water puddles will inexplicably evaporate even in the lack of sunlight.
{{Blurimage|file=Level243 2.png|caption=Photo of the sunset in Level 243. The author is unknown, most likely dead.|align=left|hovertext=Pretty beautiful sunset... isn't it?}}
<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">During the night, the following event may happen: The structure of the level will shift violently, houses will begin to overlap each other, the road will distort and warp, and holes may appear on the ground. During this event, it is worth hiding in the house, lying on the floor, and not moving. Additionally, buildings will make very loud noises of brick breaking. Because of this, there is a risk of developing hearing deficiencies; it is recommended to cover the ears. This event lasts about 30 minutes, after which everything will return to its previous state. After this, it is not recommended to go outside until the morning, to avoid the risk of falling into the ground due to its instability. If a wanderer is left outside during the night, they should find a wall, pressing themselves against it, and not move the entire time. The onset of the day can be recognized by a sharp warming, as well as by the wall clock. In the morning, all the holes in the ground will dissipate as soon as one looks away from them. After this, the '''Level 243''' will be safe once again.</span>
<div style="text-align: left"><div style="text-align: left"><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:verdana; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">''Entities''</font></div>

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">No life forms other than grass and moss were seen on '''Level 243''', most likely due to the level's anomalous and life-threatening nature. Despite this, some wanderers have reported hearing noises originating from the city and cars driving from afar. However, it is believed that these sounds are hallucinations due to a lack of '''[[Object 1|Almond Water]]''', so it is recommended to take this object to this level.<br><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:verdana; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">''Bases, Outposts and Settlements''</font></div>

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">Although there have been attempts to settle on '''Level 243''', due to the dangerous features of the level, this is almost impossible. In this level, it is impossible to meet another wanderer, as any other level affected by  [[Phenomenon 15]], even if a group of wanderers noclip into [[Level 243]] at the same time.<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:verdana; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">''Entrances and Exits''</font></div>

===<font size="5"><span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF"><u>'''Entrances'''</u></font>===

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''<s>--</s> Finding and entering the elevator on [[Level 239]] and selecting the 12<sup>th</sup> floor, the elevator will arrive on this level.'''</span>

===<font size="5"><span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF"><u>'''Exits'''</u></font>===
<div style="text-align: left">
<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF"> '''<s>--</s> In extremely rare cases, doors on houses can lead to [[Level 245]].'''</span>

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''<s>--</s> Entering the door marked "Home" will lead to the square room with a chair in it. Sitting on a chair will cause loss of consciousness. These actions will lead to [[Level 185]]''' ''(It'' ''is unknown whether this room is part of Level 243 or 185).''

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''<s>--</s> Jumping into a hole created by an instability surge leads to [[Level 173]].'''</span>

<span style="font-family:verdana; color:white; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFFFF">'''<s>--</s> Accidentally nocliping into the underground leads to [[Level 0]] or [[Level 0.66]].'''</span>

